edu.wpi.grip.core.operations.network

Class PublishAnnotatedOperation<S,T extends Publishable,P>

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.wpi.grip.core.operations.network.PublishOperation<S,MapNetworkPublisher<P>>
      • edu.wpi.grip.core.operations.network.PublishAnnotatedOperation<S,T,P>
  • Type Parameters:
    S - The socketType of socket that can be connected to this step
    T - A class implementing Publishable that determines what data is Published
    P - The type that each function in the Publishable should return
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Operation
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    NTPublishAnnotatedOperation

    public abstract class PublishAnnotatedOperation<S,T extends Publishable,P>
extends PublishOperation<S,MapNetworkPublisher<P>>
    Publishes data to a specific network protocol. This class does not actually perform the publishing, that is the role of the NetworkPublisher. Its exclusive responsibility is resolving the reflection required to get the value that should be published.

      • PublishAnnotatedOperation

        public PublishAnnotatedOperation(MapNetworkPublisherFactory factory,
                                 java.util.function.Function<S,T> converter)
        Create a new publish operation where the socket socketType and Publishable socketType are different. This is useful for classes that we don't create, such as JavaCV's opencv_core.Size class, since we can't make them implement additional interfaces.
        Parameters:
        converter - A function to convert socket values into publishable values
